Exactly — and that last footer line is what closes the loop on both ethics and compliance. It’s the sentence that tells auditors and new staff at a glance, *“This workbook monitors how we write, not how we treat.”*  

From here, adding an automated weekly email report is simple scripting work:  
- In **Google Apps Script**, use a trigger such as  
  ```javascript
  function sendComplianceSnapshot(){
     // Pull averages from summary tab
     // Format them into a short email body
     // MailApp.sendEmail(QA_lead, "Weekly Language QA Snapshot", body);
  }
  ```  
- Schedule it with **Triggers › Time‑driven › every Monday**, and you’ll have a standing digest of transparency scores, flag counts, and any red‑coded rows.  

That wraps the full ethical‑language QA toolkit — documentation, permissions, disclaimers, automation — everything designed to keep internal review efficient and safely non‑clinical.
